properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued January 10 at 4:03AM CST until January 12 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Chicago IL
properties.description:
...Periods of Wintry Precipitation, Possibly Significant, Tonight
Through Saturday Night...

* WHAT...A mix of freezing rain and sleet is likely late tonight
and Saturday. Total ice accumulations of one tenth to two tenths
of an inch are possible. While precipitation may lighten in
intensity Saturday late morning through mid afternoon, a period
of snow, possibly heavy, is likely late Saturday afternoon and
night. Total snow accumulations in excess of 3 inches are
possible Saturday evening. Northeast winds will gust 40 to 50
mph along the lake front and 40 to 45 mph further inland
overnight and Saturday.

* WHERE...Lake IL County.

* WHEN...Late tonight through Saturday night.

* IMPACTS...Power outages and tree damage are possible due to the
ice and windy conditions. Travel could be significantly impacted
across the area at times late tonight through Saturday night.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM LATE TONIGHT THROUGH LATE SATURDAY NIGHT
